{{Infobox person |name = Anna Fricke |image = Anna Fricke.jpg |caption = |birth_date = |birthname = |spouse = [[Jeremy Carver]] |birth_place = [[United States]] |occupation = [[Television writer]], [[Television producer|producer]] |yearsactive = 2001 &ndash; present }}
'''Anna Fricke''' is an American [[television writer]] and [[Television producer|producer]] best known for her work on shows like ''[[Dawson's Creek]]'', ''[[Everwood]]'', ''[[Men in Trees]]'' and ''[[Privileged (TV series)|Privileged]]'' and as the co-creator of the North American version of ''[[Being Human (North American TV series)|Being Human]]''. She is married to co-creator [[Jeremy Carver]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/35310/writers-chosen-syfys-being-human-re-imagining|title=Writers Chosen for Syfy's Being Human Re-imagining|work=Dread Central|last=Barton|first=Steve|date=January 12, 2010|accessdate=March 24, 2011}}</ref>
== Career == In 2001, Fricke served as a writer on a failed television pilot entitled ''Rachels's Room''. Since then she has worked as a writer and producer on a number of series, ''[[Dawson's Creek]]'', ''[[Everwood]]'', ''[[Men in Trees]]'' and ''[[Privileged (TV series)|Privileged]]'' among them. At the beginning of 2010 she teamed with her husband Jeremy Carver to develop a North American version of the [[United Kingdom|British]] drama series ''[[Being Human (UK TV series)|Being Human]]'', on which she served as an [[executive producer]] and [[head writer]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.film.com/celebrities/anna-fricke/14766507|title=Anna Fricke from The Beautiful Life|work=Film.com|accessdate=March 24, 2011}}</ref> The show finished at the end of its fourth season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/03/17/being-human-second-season/|title=Syfy renews 'Being Human' for second season|work=Entertainment Weekly|last=Hibberd|first=James|date=March 17, 2011|accessdate=March 24, 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110322020831/http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/03/17/being-human-second-season/| archivedate= 22 March 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
