The '''School for Poetic Computation''' ('''SFPC''') is a hybrid of a school, residency and research group that was founded in 2013<ref>{{Cite web|title = Code to Joy: The School for Poetic Computation Opens|url = http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/08/12/code-to-joy-the-school-for-poetic-computation-opens/|website = Bits Blog|accessdate = 2015-11-17}}</ref> in [[New York City|New York]]. A small group of students and faculty work closely to explore the intersections of [[code]], [[design]], [[Computer hardware|hardware]] and [[theory]]—focusing especially on [[art]]istic intervention.<ref>{{Cite web|title = SFPC {{!}} School for Poetic Computation|url = http://sfpc.io/|website = sfpc.io|accessdate = 2015-11-17}}</ref>
